### 1. Login as Fleet Manager to get token
# @name login
POST http://localhost:4000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "fleet@transitops.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Store token
@token = {{login.response.body.data.accessToken}}

### 2. Create a Vehicle (Valid)
POST http://localhost:4000/api/vehicles
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "regNo": "TEST-V-001",
  "nameModel": "Test Van",
  "type": "VAN",
  "capacityKg": 1000,
  "acquisitionCost": 20000,
  "region": "North"
}

### 3. Duplicate regNo rejection (BR-4)
POST http://localhost:4000/api/vehicles
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "regNo": "TEST-V-001",
  "nameModel": "Duplicate Van",
  "type": "VAN",
  "capacityKg": 1500,
  "acquisitionCost": 25000
}

### 4. Create an Available Driver (Valid)
POST http://localhost:4000/api/drivers
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Valid Driver",
  "licenseNo": "TEST-DL-001",
  "licenseCategory": "LMV",
  "licenseExpiry": "2030-01-01T00:00:00Z",
  "contact": "111-222"
}

### 5. Create a Driver with Expired License
POST http://localhost:4000/api/drivers
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "name": "Expired Driver",
  "licenseNo": "TEST-DL-002",
  "licenseCategory": "HMV",
  "licenseExpiry": "2020-01-01T00:00:00Z",
  "contact": "333-444"
}

### 6. Get Available Drivers (Should exclude Expired Driver)
GET http://localhost:4000/api/drivers?status=AVAILABLE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
